==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Misprize
<hw>Mis*prize"</hw> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧s*pr⟦imac⟧z")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[OF. <ets>mesprisier</ets> to deprise, F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧priser</ets>; pref. amiss, wrong (L. <ets>minus</ets> less
+ LL. <ets>pretium</ets> price. See <er>price</er>, <er>Prize</er>,
<pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>To slight or undervalue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, for those vanished hours, so much <qex>misprized</qex>!</q>
<rj><qau>Hillhouse.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I do not blame them, madam, nor <qex>misprize</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misproceeding</ent>⟦br⟧
